        • [ - ] jesper - member since 13-Feb-15

          The Santiago Bernabu will observe a minutes silence before the start of this match and the Real Madrid players will wear black armbands in memory of Henning Jensen, who passed away two days ago. Im so glad the club will honour a deceaced former player this way. As a kid I looked up to Henning Jensen, even wrote an essay on him at school (probably not very good) to express my admiration. He came out of nothing - played in a regional league in Denmark when he was selected to the national team that succefully qualified Denmark for the OL 1972. He was a streetplayer who taught himself how to use his skills - and these skills were so obvious that he became a national team-player and signed with Borrussia Mnchengladbach though he had never played for any club at a higher level than the fourth best Danish league. As a professional he won national championships with Borrussia Mnchengladbach, Real Madrid and Ajax Amsterdam. When the whole Santiago Bernabu honours him tonight so will I.
